35)Write a PHP script using an array that checks if a string contains another string and
displays the result.
<?php
$mainString = "Welcome to Marvel Motors car workshop in Coimbatore.";
$subStrings = array("Marvel", "car", "service", "Coimbatore", "bike");
foreach ($subStrings as $sub)
if (strpos($mainString, $sub) !== false) {
echo "The string contains '$sub'.<br>";
} else {
echo "The string does NOT contain '$sub'.<br>";
}
}
?>
output:
The string contains 'Marvel'.
The string contains 'car'.
The string does NOT contain 'service'.
The string contains 'Coimbatore'.
The string does NOT contain 'bike'.
